    <name>Gameyfin Desktop</name>
    <summary>A dedicated desktop client for Gameyfin</summary>
    <description>
        <p>
            Gameyfin Desktop is a dedicated desktop client for Gameyfin that wraps the web interface
            in a standalone application for a more integrated experience.
        </p>
        <p>Key Features:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Dedicated Desktop Application:</strong>
                Runs Gameyfin in its own window, separate from your web browser.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Persistent SSO Login:</strong>
                Supports persistent logins with SSO providers. The application saves your session data, so you only have
                to log in once.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>System Tray Integration:</strong>
                Includes an icon in the system tray for quickly showing, hiding, or quitting the application.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Integrated Settings:</strong>
            Configure your Gameyfin URL, window dimensions, and more directly within the app.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Download Manager:</strong>
                Manages all file downloads in a persistent "Downloads" tab, showing progress, speed, and history.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Linux Installer:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Prompts for per-install environment configuration (Wayland, GameID, Store, etc.).</li>
                    <li>Extracts the downloaded archive and detects .exe files.</li>
                    <li>Automatically looks up the umu-id for proton fixes.</li>
                    <li>Automatically creates a wineprefix and launches the installer using umu-run.</li>
                    <li>Quick access to winecfg and winetricks for manual prefix configuration.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Integrated Shortcut Management:</strong>
                Automatically detects shortcuts created by the installer and allows you to add them to your Desktop and
                Application Menu.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </description>
